#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Each package must have a `composer.json` file in its root directory. At minimum, define a package name, dependencies, autoloading, and Yii config metadata when the package integrates with a Yii application."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Use a package name in the `vendor-name/project-name` format:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (json)
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"name\": \"vendor/blog\",\n"
"    \"type\": \"library\",\n"
"    \"description\": \"Blog integration for Yii applications\",\n"
"    \"require\": {\n"
"        \"php\": \">=8.2\",\n"
"        \"yiisoft/router\": \"^4.0\"\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"autoload\": {\n"
"        \"psr-4\": {\n"
"            \"Vendor\\\\Blog\\\\\": \"src/\"\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Use stable dependency constraints for stable releases. Avoid using `yiisoft` as your vendor name because it is reserved for Yii packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "If your package requires a Yii application, prefixing the project name with `yii-` can make that clear on Packagist."
msgstr ""

