msgstr "包"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "A Yii-aware package is a regular Composer package with PHP classes, optional resource files, and optional config files.  Keep the configuration in a predictable directory and make the public API explicit:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"composer.json\n"
"config/\n"
"    params.php\n"
"    di.php\n"
"    di-providers.php\n"
"    routes.php\n"
"    events.php\n"
"    params-web.php\n"
"    params-console.php\n"
"    di-console.php\n"
"src/\n"
"    ...\n"
"assets/\n"
"    ...\n"
"migrations/\n"
"    ...\n"
"messages/\n"
"    ...\n"
"views/\n"
"    ...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Use only the files your package needs. For example, a package with console commands but no web routes does not need `routes.php`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Config plugin"
msgid "Config plugin metadata"
msgstr "配置插件"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Yii applications use [yiisoft/config](https://github.com/yiisoft/config) to discover package configuration.  Declare package config files in the `extra.config-plugin` section of `composer.json`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (json)
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"name\": \"vendor/blog\",\n"
"    \"type\": \"library\",\n"
"    \"autoload\": {\n"
"        \"psr-4\": {\n"
"            \"Vendor\\\\Blog\\\\\": \"src/\"\n"
"        }\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"extra\": {\n"
"        \"config-plugin\": {\n"
"            \"params\": \"config/params.php\",\n"
"            \"di\": \"config/di.php\",\n"
"            \"di-providers\": \"config/di-providers.php\",\n"
"            \"routes\": \"config/routes.php\",\n"
"            \"events\": \"config/events.php\",\n"
"            \"params-web\": \"config/params-web.php\",\n"
"            \"params-console\": \"config/params-console.php\",\n"
"            \"di-console\": \"config/di-console.php\"\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Each `config-plugin` key is a config group name and each value is a path relative to the package root."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Use the common, web, and console groups consistently:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "`params`, `di`, `di-providers`, `di-delegates`, `events`, and `bootstrap` apply to both web and console entry points."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "`params-web`, `di-web`, `di-providers-web`, `events-web`, `bootstrap-web`, and `routes` apply to web entry points."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "`params-console`, `di-console`, `di-providers-console`, `events-console`, and `bootstrap-console` apply to console entry points."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "If your package defines a new config group, document how an application should load that group. Prefer the standard groups when you integrate with Yii services because application templates and Yii packages already use these names."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "After users install, update, remove, or dump Composer autoload files, the config plugin rebuilds the merge plan that Yii reads at runtime. If users edit their root package configuration manually, ask them to run:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Put default options in `config/params.php`. Group package parameters under the Composer package name to avoid collisions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<?php\n"
"\n"
"declare(strict_types=1);\n"
"\n"
"return [\n"
"    'vendor/blog' => [\n"
"        'postsPerPage' => 20,\n"
"        'cacheTtl' => 3600,\n"
"    ],\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Application developers can override these values in their own `config/common/params.php`, `config/web/params.php`, `config/console/params.php`, or environment-specific parameter files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Do not read environment variables or global state from package code when a parameter can express the choice. Use parameters to configure services through DI definitions or service providers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Definitions"
msgid "DI definitions"
msgstr "定义"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Use `config/di.php`, `config/di-web.php`, or `config/di-console.php` for direct container definitions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<?php\n"
"\n"
"declare(strict_types=1);\n"
"\n"
"use Vendor\\Blog\\PostRepository;\n"
"use Vendor\\Blog\\PostRepositoryInterface;\n"
"\n"
"/** @var array $params */\n"
"\n"
"return [\n"
"    PostRepositoryInterface::class => [\n"
"        'class' => PostRepository::class,\n"
"        '__construct()' => [\n"
"            'cacheTtl' => $params['vendor/blog']['cacheTtl'],\n"
"        ],\n"
"    ],\n"
"];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Prefer direct DI definitions when the configuration describes one service clearly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Service providers"
msgid "DI service providers"
msgstr "服务提供者"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
msgid "Use a DI provider when registration belongs together as a reusable unit: several related services, aliases, factory definitions, or extensions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Adjust `config/common/routes.php`:"
msgid "Register providers in `config/di-providers.php`:"
msgstr "调整 `config/common/routes.php`："

#. type: Fenced code block (php)
#: ../src/guide/structure/designing-packages.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<?php\n"
"\n"
"declare(strict_types=1);\n"
"\n"
"use Vendor\\Blog\\Provider\\BlogProvider;\n"
"\n"
"return [\n"
"    'vendor/blog/post-repository' => BlogProvider::class,\n"
"];\n"
